<topic template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2022-03-21T12:15:23.711Z" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Why do I need to add Geometry to the Base-Part?</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>BasePart<keyword>Why Not Geometry in BasePart?</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Why do I need to add Geometry to the Base-Part?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Where is the Base-Part Geometry?</para>
    <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Why is there not a <text styleclass="Element">CAD-Line</text> in the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-BasePart" styleclass="Element">Base-Part</link>?<text style="font-weight:bold;"> </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We do not want you to <text style="text-decoration:underline;">automatically</text> add Joints to the Origin, X-axis or Y–axis of the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text> (and Mechanism Axes).</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo2">However, you are welcome to do this.</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why?<text style="font-weight:bold;"> </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">For the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>, we have found it to be useful to add <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> that are <text style="text-decoration:underline;">not</text> at the Origin or along the X-axis or Y–axis. We then add dimensions to give the position of the Points and Lines relative to the origin of the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>.</para>
    <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why?<text style="font-weight:bold;"> </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can <text style="text-decoration:underline;">edit</text> the dimensions later, and also add them to a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-FB-DesignSet">Design-Set</link>.</para>
    <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why edit <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> in the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Parts</text>?<text style="font-weight:bold;"> </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You have the design flexibility to:</para>
    <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%0:s." format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Move the Joints, if the <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> or <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> are used for Joints<text style="font-weight:bold;"> </text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Move the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text> in the Machine Frame, if a <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> is used for a new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> and then <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>.</li>
    </list>
  </body>
</topic>
